Deprecated. replaced by more flexible map based script processors: ScriptFilterProcessor

public class JavascriptFilterProcessor
extends JavascriptProcessor

Extend JavascriptProcessor to filter records based on the result of script execution.
This processor differes from JavascriptProcessor in that it uses the result of the javascript execution to filter records.
It expects the javascript to return a Boolean result, which dictates whether a given record passes through or is discarded by the processor.
Default behaviour is to discard records where the javascript returns true. This may be overridden by the discartMatches property.

getDiscardMatches

public boolean getDiscardMatches()
Deprecated. 
Returns true (default) if this processor will discard records where the javascript has returned true.
Unsurprisingly returns false otherwise.

setDiscardMatches

public void setDiscardMatches(boolean discardMatches)
Deprecated. 
Configure discard behaviour for this processor.
If set to true (the default), it will discard records where the javascript evaluates to true.
If set to false, it will discard records where the javascript evaluates to false.

Parameters:
discardMatches - boolean containing true to discard matches, false otherwise.

generateOutput

protected java.lang.Object[] generateOutput(JavascriptProcessor.JavascriptResult jsResult)
Deprecated. 
Generate output record array whose contents depend on the supplied JavascriptResult. This overrides the superclass default behaviour in that it examines the result of the evaulated javascript and either returns the output record, or discards it depending on that result. The resultant output will either be an empty Object[] or one containing a single value - the output record from the javascript result.
It expects the javascript to return a Boolean value. If not it will throw a RuntimeException.
